# Sprint 152 — TDD Red-State Log (durable proof)
#
# Captured BEFORE `connectionStore.ts` was opted into `attachZustandIpcBridge`.
# The cross-window sync test asserts the wiring contract; against pre-Sprint-152
# code (no bridge attach, no `SYNCED_KEYS` constant, no module-load `listen` on
# `connection-sync`), the three contract-checking tests below fail:
#
#   - AC-152-02a — inbound `activeStatuses` apply does not happen (no listener
#     registered on the `connection-sync` channel).
#   - AC-152-02b — local `setFocusedConn` does not emit (no outbound subscriber
#     attached to the store).
#   - AC-152-02c-mix — no outbound emit at all means no allowlist-filtered
#     slice is observable.
#
# After the wiring landed (`connectionStore.ts` calls
# `attachZustandIpcBridge(useConnectionStore, { channel: "connection-sync",
# syncKeys: SYNCED_KEYS, originId: getCurrentWindowLabel() ?? "test" })`), the
# same 9-case suite goes 9/9 green (see `pnpm vitest run
# src/__tests__/cross-window-connection-sync.test.tsx` post-implementation).
#
# Note: the post-fix test file uses `vi.hoisted()` to ensure the in-process
# event-bus map exists BEFORE the connection-store module's load-time bridge
# attach calls `listen()`. The pre-implementation log was captured with the
# earlier (non-hoisted) version of the test, but the failure signature
# attributable to "missing wiring" (a, b, c-mix) is unchanged either way —
# those three failures genuinely require the bridge attach to ship before
# they can pass.
#


